description.plain:
Jack & Jack are a musical duo hailing from Omaha, Nebraska who got their claim to fame by posting 6-second videos on the popular social media app, Vine. Jack Gilinsky and Jack J have been friends since their first day of kindergarten.

Following the collaborative tour of Magcon, Jack & Jack began to release music such as Tides – then moving onto better-produced tracks like Wild Life and Cold Hearted to name a few.

In July 2015, the duo released their first EP titled Calibraska, joining their state of origin and where they currently live along with the lead single California.

In May 2017, Jack & Jack released their second EP titled Gone.

In January 2019, Jack & Jack released their debut album titled A Good Friend Is Nice.

songs.title: 2 Cigarettes

description.plain:
In “2 Cigarettes,” Jack & Jack depict the failing relationship, which was described in the previous song off the EP, “Hurt People.” The damage are so detrimental that it drives him to smoke two cigarettes even though he doesn’t smoke, looking for anything to alleviate the pain.

This is Jack Johnson’s favorite song off the project.

songs.full_title: No One Compares to You by Jack & Jack
songs.title: No One Compares to You

description.plain:
“No One Compares to You” is Jack & Jack’s first release after achieving global acclaim featuring on Jonas Blue’s summer smash hit “Rise”. This track marks their third demo after “Rise” and their 2017’s “Beg”. Writer Jake Torrey approached them with the idea for this song and the trio went on to write the track “Barcelona” for their upcoming album.

They explained that “Rise” was the first time a lot of people outside of their fanbase had heard their music, and they wanted to “ease them into the world of Jack & Jack” by continuing the “tropical vibe”. “No One Compares to You” was originally all-acoustic, so they provided DJ Khaled’s sensation “I’m The One” as a reference for it’s reproduction. They felt its upbeat, feel-good nature would allow them to reach their goal of another radio hit.

The song details a subject who loves a girl but is unable to get her.  They try to replace her, but fail because they can’t find anyone good enough.

songs.title: Hurt People

description.plain:
The relationship between the two  lovers is fading. The girl who was hurt by the man she was in love with before, is now hurting her new boyfriend. She reproducing what she experienced before : it’s a vicious circle. The lover is also going to hurt someone after being hurt by the girl, etc.
The boy was previously becoming crazy because he was deeply in love with the girl but now he is crazy as she can’t make up her mind and make him suffer.
